1
00:00:10,633 --> 00:00:14,633
<i> Why are women ghosting men?</i>

2
00:00:14,767 --> 00:00:16,367
<i>You're talking about
Doc Cecilia, right?</i>

3
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:17,433
<i> She has a boyfriend.</i>

4
00:00:17,567 --> 00:00:20,033
<i> It's Vice Mayor Glen Guerrero.</i>

5
00:00:20,167 --> 00:00:20,733
<i> Come on!</i>

6
00:00:20,867 --> 00:00:22,133
<i> Okay, Sir.</i>

7
00:00:22,267 --> 00:00:25,267
<i>If you want, ask Doc Cecilia,
so she can tell you the truth.</i>

8
00:00:25,400 --> 00:00:27,567
<i>Because it's hard to be led on.</i>

9
00:00:27,700 --> 00:00:29,767
<i>You're being transferred
to San Isidro, Batangas.</i>

10
00:00:29,900 --> 00:00:31,333
<i> Be good there, okay?</i>

11
00:00:31,467 --> 00:00:33,367
<i> Mando, it's under the seat.</i>

12
00:00:34,333 --> 00:00:36,067
<i>Sir, Romel is having
a heart attack!</i>

13
00:00:40,400 --> 00:00:41,467
<i> Hurry! Hurry!</i>

14
00:00:43,133 --> 00:00:45,333
<i>- Let's go! Let's go!
- Let's go! Let's go!</i>

15
00:00:46,333 --> 00:00:47,867
<i>Go and escape!
I'll take care of this!</i>

16
00:00:51,433 --> 00:00:53,400
<i>One of the inmates
is Mandong Warak.</i>

17
00:00:53,533 --> 00:00:54,867
<i>Wait, you're a fugitive, right?</i>

18
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:56,467
<i> Is that obvious?</i>

19
00:00:56,600 --> 00:00:58,967
<i>He's very notorious
for killing policemen.</i>

20
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:01,733
<i>Oh my, good luck to Garcia
if he escapes.</i>

21
00:01:01,867 --> 00:01:03,000
<i> He might be the next victim.</i>

22
00:01:03,133 --> 00:01:05,000
<i>Alpha, this is
Sergeant Bobby Enriquez.</i>

23
00:01:05,133 --> 00:01:06,800
<i>I'll respond.
I'm just near the location.</i>

24
00:01:06,933 --> 00:01:08,367
<i> Enriquez will respond alone?</i>

25
00:01:08,533 --> 00:01:10,100
<i> Come on, let's join her.</i>

26
00:02:20,833 --> 00:02:24,300
Let's party!

27
00:02:40,067 --> 00:02:41,833
Major...

28
00:02:41,967 --> 00:02:45,167
how's the situation at Marilag?

29
00:02:45,300 --> 00:02:47,167
Do you have the prisoners
under control?

30
00:02:47,300 --> 00:02:49,333
Mayor, there's no official
report yet,

31
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:50,733
but someone has responded.

32
00:02:50,867 --> 00:02:52,133
It's Sergeant Enriquez.

33
00:02:52,267 --> 00:02:53,433
What?

34
00:02:53,567 --> 00:02:54,700
Bobby?

35
00:02:54,833 --> 00:02:56,133
My daughter?

36
00:02:56,267 --> 00:02:57,367
Who's with her?

37
00:02:57,500 --> 00:02:58,900
She's alone, Mayor,

38
00:02:59,033 --> 00:03:00,200
but someone is on the way there.

39
00:03:00,333 --> 00:03:03,567
Major, please make sure
that my daughter is safe.

40
00:03:03,700 --> 00:03:04,733
Let me know right away.

41
00:03:04,867 --> 00:03:05,767
Yes, Mayor.

42
00:03:05,900 --> 00:03:07,500
I'll update you.

43
00:03:10,533 --> 00:03:14,033
Do you really need to endorse
that woman to the major?

44
00:03:14,167 --> 00:03:15,333
How old is she?

45
00:03:15,467 --> 00:03:16,467
Nine years old?

46
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:18,367
She's still my daughter!

47
00:03:18,500 --> 00:03:20,633
She's going to face a criminal!

48
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:25,033
I would have done the same
with Glen and Faye!

49
00:03:25,167 --> 00:03:27,233
What's the issue?

50
00:03:27,367 --> 00:03:29,167
I still haven't forgiven you,

51
00:03:29,300 --> 00:03:32,133
when you tried to include
that girl in our family.

52
00:03:32,267 --> 00:03:34,967
And now, you're still spreading
the word to other people...

53
00:03:35,100 --> 00:03:37,567
that you have a child
with another woman?

54
00:03:37,700 --> 00:03:41,667
Even asking special treatment
for that bastard!

55
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:43,333
She's still my daughter!

56
00:03:43,467 --> 00:03:45,667
Is it wrong for me to think
about her safety?

57
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:49,333
Our lives are quiet, Joaquin.

58
00:03:49,467 --> 00:03:53,400
I forgave you
when you loved Alicia.

59
00:03:53,533 --> 00:03:56,967
And now, you keep hurting me
over and over again...

60
00:03:57,133 --> 00:04:02,167
every time you think of that
bastard daughter of yours!

61
00:04:02,300 --> 00:04:03,733
Sophia!

62
00:04:14,067 --> 00:04:16,167
This is Enriquez's car.

63
00:04:16,300 --> 00:04:18,200
I'm sure she needs our help.

64
00:04:18,333 --> 00:04:21,700
Maybe it's better if we split up
so we can find her faster.

65
00:04:21,833 --> 00:04:23,100
Okay, I'll go here.

66
00:04:23,233 --> 00:04:24,633
Okay.

67
00:04:57,900 --> 00:04:59,400
Count it first.

68
00:05:02,233 --> 00:05:03,333
Bro, call Boss Tonyo.

69
00:05:03,467 --> 00:05:05,167
It seems like there's an
exchange going on here.

70
00:05:10,300 --> 00:05:12,267
Okay, take care.

71
00:05:15,833 --> 00:05:17,567
Bro! Bro, Jako has left.

72
00:05:17,700 --> 00:05:19,033
What are we going to do?

73
00:05:19,167 --> 00:05:21,600
Sir Tonyo isn't answering.

74
00:05:21,733 --> 00:05:23,733
We need to talk to that guy.

75
00:05:40,667 --> 00:05:41,867
Hey, stop!

76
00:05:43,567 --> 00:05:44,433
You think you can escape, huh?

77
00:05:44,567 --> 00:05:46,033
Go there!

78
00:06:00,300 --> 00:06:01,333
Hey!

79
00:06:12,733 --> 00:06:13,767
You fool!

80
00:06:17,967 --> 00:06:19,800
You're out of bullets?

81
00:06:19,933 --> 00:06:22,000
Throw it away! That's no use!

82
00:06:22,133 --> 00:06:24,000
That's the problem with you.

83
00:06:24,133 --> 00:06:26,900
You keep on shooting,
but you're not aiming!

84
00:06:29,133 --> 00:06:31,700
You really think
you can steal this?

85
00:06:31,833 --> 00:06:33,133
You thought you were fast?

86
00:06:33,267 --> 00:06:35,233
Well, I'm faster than you.

87
00:06:35,367 --> 00:06:37,333
What do you think of me? Stupid?

88
00:06:41,367 --> 00:06:42,967
That was close.

89
00:06:43,100 --> 00:06:45,867
You keep trying to hit me,
but your arms are too short.

90
00:06:59,333 --> 00:07:01,000
Surrender properly.

91
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:03,133
Come here.

92
00:07:06,233 --> 00:07:08,800
There. I'll make sure
you won't be able to shoot.

93
00:07:08,933 --> 00:07:09,733
Stand up!

94
00:07:09,867 --> 00:07:11,333
I'll bring you back to jail!

95
00:07:11,467 --> 00:07:13,533
Stand up!

96
00:07:13,667 --> 00:07:15,533
Don't even think about doing
anything stupid.

97
00:07:15,700 --> 00:07:17,400
Don't come near me!

98
00:07:17,533 --> 00:07:18,900
Turn around!

99
00:07:20,767 --> 00:07:21,733
Okay, okay, okay.

100
00:07:21,867 --> 00:07:23,933
Make sure you won't do
anything stupid.

101
00:07:24,067 --> 00:07:25,667
Go! Walk!

102
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:27,033
Walk!

103
00:07:28,967 --> 00:07:30,533
Bok!

104
00:07:30,667 --> 00:07:31,733
Kneel. Kneel down, kneel!

105
00:07:31,867 --> 00:07:33,767
Kneel. Kneel down, kneel!

106
00:07:35,967 --> 00:07:37,300
Have you seen Enriquez?

107
00:07:37,433 --> 00:07:42,100
No, but I saw a fool who thought
he was faster than me.

108
00:07:50,867 --> 00:07:52,700
Are you looking for me?

109
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:57,633
Perfect timing, I'm going
to use my new weapon.

110
00:08:00,833 --> 00:08:01,567
That's from there.

111
00:08:01,700 --> 00:08:03,300
Maybe it's Enriquez.

112
00:08:03,433 --> 00:08:05,433
Bok, you take care
of this first.

113
00:08:05,567 --> 00:08:06,733
I'll find Enriquez.

114
00:08:06,867 --> 00:08:07,800
Okay, Bok.

115
00:08:52,133 --> 00:08:53,800
Enriquez!

116
00:08:57,033 --> 00:08:58,600
Enriquez!

117
00:09:05,433 --> 00:09:07,633
The PDL models are now being
transferred

118
00:09:07,767 --> 00:09:09,333
from Calabari State Prison

119
00:09:09,467 --> 00:09:12,633
to a new state-of-the-art
facility in Batangas.

120
00:09:12,767 --> 00:09:16,067
We're going to ask the Calabari
State University community.

121
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:20,067
Do they believe that PDLs
have the heart to change?

122
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:23,500
Or is punishment enough to pay
for their misdeeds?

123
00:09:23,633 --> 00:09:25,767
Sorry. Cut, Faye.

124
00:09:25,900 --> 00:09:27,633
Your face looks oily,
doesn't it?

125
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:29,800
And also your pimple,
it's so obvious, girl.

126
00:09:29,933 --> 00:09:31,233
Yes, it's a bit...

127
00:09:31,367 --> 00:09:32,933
-Wait, wait, here, here.
-It's very visible on the video.

128
00:09:33,067 --> 00:09:34,000
Just do a retouch.

129
00:09:34,133 --> 00:09:35,900
Okay. Is it okay
if I do my retouch?

130
00:09:36,033 --> 00:09:37,733
I'll just borrow your stuff.

131
00:09:37,867 --> 00:09:39,433
Okay. It's okay.

132
00:09:39,567 --> 00:09:41,300
- Okay.
- We'll just go to the restroom.

133
00:09:41,433 --> 00:09:42,767
- Sis, come with me.
- Yes.

134
00:09:42,900 --> 00:09:45,467
Sissy, I'll just buy some food.

135
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:46,800
Just wait.

136
00:10:02,533 --> 00:10:03,800
Bro, Faye's calling.

137
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:06,867
Can you answer that later?

138
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:08,600
It's Faye, Bro.

139
00:10:11,067 --> 00:10:12,200
Hello?

140
00:10:12,333 --> 00:10:14,333
Vince, are you on your way?

141
00:10:14,467 --> 00:10:16,000
This will just be a quick
interview.

142
00:10:16,133 --> 00:10:19,333
Not yet, Will and I
are just doing something.

143
00:10:19,467 --> 00:10:21,433
Oh, really now?

144
00:10:21,567 --> 00:10:23,233
Are you mad?

145
00:10:23,367 --> 00:10:26,033
Oh, sorry, sorry, not you.

146
00:10:26,167 --> 00:10:30,167
I have a pimple right now,

147
00:10:30,300 --> 00:10:32,400
and we're currently
shooting some spiels.

148
00:10:32,533 --> 00:10:33,367
That's okay,

149
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:35,600
you're still pretty
even with a pimple.

150
00:10:35,767 --> 00:10:38,200
Vince, do that later, he's here!

151
00:10:38,333 --> 00:10:39,733
Hey, what are you doing?

152
00:10:39,867 --> 00:10:40,833
Okay, okay, okay.

153
00:10:40,967 --> 00:10:42,567
- Bye.
- Hello?

154
00:10:46,100 --> 00:10:47,200
Bro, it's okay.

155
00:10:48,467 --> 00:10:49,967
Okay, Sir.

156
00:10:50,100 --> 00:10:52,067
Boss, just a moment.

157
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:53,600
What is it?

158
00:10:53,733 --> 00:10:57,867
We just want to ask you
about the money given to you.

159
00:11:00,500 --> 00:11:01,733
Hey!

160
00:11:12,367 --> 00:11:14,667
There, perfect!
There's a pimple patch.

161
00:11:29,100 --> 00:11:30,100
Perfect.

162
00:11:53,700 --> 00:11:55,333
- Hey, hey!
- Hey, stop!

163
00:11:55,467 --> 00:11:56,600
Hey, stop!

164
00:12:01,833 --> 00:12:02,767
Help!

165
00:12:02,900 --> 00:12:04,167
Robbers! Help!

166
00:12:04,300 --> 00:12:06,133
What do you mean?
You're the bad guy here!

167
00:12:06,267 --> 00:12:07,667
I'm not doing anything wrong!

168
00:12:07,800 --> 00:12:10,267
You're the one who asked
about the money given to me!

169
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:12,467
We saw you talking to Jako.

170
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:13,933
He gave you some money.
What was that for?

171
00:12:14,100 --> 00:12:15,033
Did you make a sale?

172
00:12:15,167 --> 00:12:17,000
What sale?

173
00:12:17,133 --> 00:12:18,600
I don't know
what you're talking about!

174
00:12:18,733 --> 00:12:21,267
What? Are you the one supplying
Jako's party drugs?

175
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:23,400
What drugs? I don't know
anything about that!

176
00:12:23,533 --> 00:12:25,567
The pimple patch drugs!

177
00:12:25,700 --> 00:12:27,867
Jako is involved because
he's Monty's brother.

178
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:29,733
He's the one who was caught
selling them.

179
00:12:29,867 --> 00:12:31,667
I know Monty,

180
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:34,500
but I have nothing to do
with his business,

181
00:12:34,633 --> 00:12:36,333
especially Jako.

182
00:12:36,467 --> 00:12:40,967
Jako gives me money to support
my son's dialysis!

183
00:12:41,100 --> 00:12:42,000
Don't fool us!

184
00:12:42,133 --> 00:12:43,300
Why would he do that?

185
00:12:44,567 --> 00:12:46,467
Jako is a good kid.

186
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:47,400
I used to be the janitor here

187
00:12:47,533 --> 00:12:48,767
when they were still
in high school.

188
00:12:48,933 --> 00:12:52,467
Even before, Monty was always
the bad guy.

189
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:56,000
But Jako was very different
from his brother.

190
00:12:56,133 --> 00:13:00,900
Jako had nothing to do
with those party drugs.

191
00:13:09,267 --> 00:13:11,000
Enriquez!

192
00:13:15,033 --> 00:13:15,933
Enriquez...

193
00:13:20,333 --> 00:13:21,433
What happened to you?

194
00:13:25,267 --> 00:13:27,933
Faye, this just in.

195
00:13:28,067 --> 00:13:31,733
The Calabari inmates' vehicle
was hijacked.

196
00:13:31,867 --> 00:13:34,267
Some inmates escaped.

197
00:13:34,400 --> 00:13:36,267
Is this true?

198
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:39,100
I don't know,
I don't know about that.

199
00:13:39,233 --> 00:13:41,433
You know, Jhem and Anika
are taking so long.

200
00:13:41,567 --> 00:13:42,400
They're taking so long.

201
00:13:42,533 --> 00:13:43,733
Let's just get that started.

202
00:13:43,867 --> 00:13:45,033
Hurry up, stand up.

203
00:13:45,167 --> 00:13:47,067
- Let's start this report.
- Wait, wait.

204
00:13:48,367 --> 00:13:49,867
Game.

205
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:52,333
I'm ready. Game.

206
00:13:52,467 --> 00:13:53,667
This is taking so long. Come on.

207
00:13:53,800 --> 00:13:55,500
Just wait.
Okay, are you ready?

208
00:13:55,667 --> 00:13:56,500
Ready, ready.

209
00:13:56,633 --> 00:13:59,533
Okay, one, two, three, go.

210
00:13:59,667 --> 00:14:01,100
Hi, guys!

211
00:14:01,233 --> 00:14:02,933
Surprise!

212
00:14:03,067 --> 00:14:07,533
You know what? As we speak,
some inmates have escaped

213
00:14:07,667 --> 00:14:11,167
and are currently on the loose
here in Calabari.

214
00:14:11,300 --> 00:14:12,700
How fun!

215
00:14:12,833 --> 00:14:16,033
Welcome to the free world,
inmates!

216
00:14:16,167 --> 00:14:17,567
Let's just let them go.

217
00:14:17,700 --> 00:14:20,067
Whatever would make them happy,
then go! Right?

218
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:21,233
They're running.

219
00:14:21,367 --> 00:14:22,167
There, see.

220
00:14:22,300 --> 00:14:25,567
Hello! Bye!

221
00:14:25,700 --> 00:14:27,533
- Hello!
- Faye! Faye!

222
00:14:27,700 --> 00:14:29,800
Are you okay?

223
00:14:29,933 --> 00:14:32,200
What are you talking about?

224
00:14:32,333 --> 00:14:33,833
That's not in our script.

225
00:14:33,967 --> 00:14:35,033
I know that.

226
00:14:35,167 --> 00:14:38,400
Let's improvise because they're
fugitives already.

227
00:14:38,533 --> 00:14:41,600
And I'm sorry, I'm really sorry.

228
00:14:41,733 --> 00:14:43,667
Because it's all their fault,

229
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:45,200
and if they die,

230
00:14:45,333 --> 00:14:46,700
it's because the police
are chasing them.

231
00:14:46,833 --> 00:14:48,267
Because...

232
00:14:48,400 --> 00:14:49,400
they'll be shot at!

233
00:14:49,533 --> 00:14:50,933
Police! Like that, like that.

234
00:14:51,067 --> 00:14:52,200
Then they hide again.

235
00:14:52,333 --> 00:14:53,467
Then that's it,
they'll shoot again.

236
00:14:53,600 --> 00:14:55,467
Then they'll go around here.

237
00:14:55,600 --> 00:14:56,600
Then...

238
00:14:58,133 --> 00:14:59,167
Then they'll hide again.

239
00:14:59,300 --> 00:15:00,567
Then like this, like that.

240
00:15:00,700 --> 00:15:03,267
Like this, and then...

241
00:15:03,433 --> 00:15:06,000
Faye!

242
00:15:06,133 --> 00:15:07,567
- Help! Faye!
- Faye!

243
00:15:07,700 --> 00:15:09,600
Faye! Help! Faye!

244
00:15:09,733 --> 00:15:11,100
- Help!
- Faye...

245
00:15:11,233 --> 00:15:12,900
- What's going on here?
- Sir Chito, it's Faye!

246
00:15:13,033 --> 00:15:14,700
Faye! Move, move!

247
00:15:14,833 --> 00:15:16,367
Faye!

248
00:15:16,500 --> 00:15:17,500
- Faye!
- Faye!

249
00:15:17,633 --> 00:15:19,267
- Faye!
- Wake up...

250
00:15:19,400 --> 00:15:20,667
Faye, what happened?

251
00:15:20,800 --> 00:15:21,867
What happened here?

252
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:24,200
I don't know, Sir Chito!

253
00:15:26,233 --> 00:15:27,300
Enriquez!

254
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:29,433
Wake up!

255
00:15:32,367 --> 00:15:33,933
- Sir...
- Are you okay?

256
00:15:35,867 --> 00:15:37,467
I fought back, Sir.

257
00:15:43,533 --> 00:15:48,233
It's better to just wait
for backup to arrive.

258
00:15:48,367 --> 00:15:50,133
I'll look for the other inmates.

259
00:15:51,467 --> 00:15:52,400
Okay, Sir.

260
00:15:52,533 --> 00:15:53,900
Be careful, okay?

261
00:15:54,033 --> 00:15:55,200
They're armed.

262
00:15:57,333 --> 00:15:58,933
Okay, Sir.

263
00:16:07,467 --> 00:16:10,000
We apologize for hurting you.

264
00:16:10,167 --> 00:16:11,867
It's okay.

265
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:14,767
If Jako isn't the new supplier
of the pimple patch drugs,

266
00:16:14,900 --> 00:16:16,300
then who is it?

267
00:16:16,433 --> 00:16:19,400
All I know is that Monty
has a girlfriend.

268
00:16:19,533 --> 00:16:22,033
She's also studying
at the university.

269
00:16:22,167 --> 00:16:25,167
Based on our intel,
he doesn't have a girlfriend.

270
00:16:25,300 --> 00:16:28,467
He does, they're just not out
in the open.

271
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:33,133
They're banned because his
girlfriend is too young.

272
00:16:33,267 --> 00:16:35,133
Their age gap is too big.

273
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:41,833
Clean that up.

274
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:44,800
Remove all the clutter
from this room.

275
00:16:44,933 --> 00:16:46,600
Sir, I can't do this alone.

276
00:16:46,733 --> 00:16:48,733
You can do it.

277
00:17:09,600 --> 00:17:10,600
Hello, Babe?

278
00:17:10,733 --> 00:17:11,767
How are you?

279
00:17:11,900 --> 00:17:13,000
I miss you.

280
00:17:13,133 --> 00:17:15,433
I miss you too.

281
00:17:15,600 --> 00:17:16,833
Babe...

282
00:17:16,967 --> 00:17:19,300
can't I really come visit
you there?

283
00:17:19,433 --> 00:17:20,333
No.

284
00:17:20,467 --> 00:17:21,933
No one should know
that we know each other.

285
00:17:22,067 --> 00:17:24,500
I don't want to sell
the pimple patches anymore.

286
00:17:24,633 --> 00:17:26,867
It's too dangerous.

287
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:29,300
Besides, you know
I'm only doing this

288
00:17:29,433 --> 00:17:33,367
so that your supplier can help
you get out of prison, right?

289
00:17:33,500 --> 00:17:35,633
Babe, that's still money.

290
00:17:35,767 --> 00:17:37,133
No one will think
that you're the main seller

291
00:17:37,267 --> 00:17:38,367
at the university.

292
00:17:38,500 --> 00:17:41,567
Babe, if I get caught,
I'll go to jail.

293
00:17:45,667 --> 00:17:47,367
Jhem!

294
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:52,567
You're just here! I've been
looking for you for a while!

295
00:17:52,700 --> 00:17:55,067
Mom, okay. I'll just text you
later, okay?

296
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:56,933
- Bye.
- Okay, okay.

297
00:17:57,067 --> 00:17:58,633
Let's just talk later.

298
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:01,867
Why?

299
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:03,533
Something happened to Faye.

300
00:18:04,467 --> 00:18:05,567
What happened?

301
00:18:08,233 --> 00:18:09,567
Stop!

302
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:12,633
Don't run!

303
00:18:12,767 --> 00:18:14,200
I'll shoot you!

304
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:16,933
Raise your hand.

305
00:18:21,233 --> 00:18:22,733
Surrender properly.

306
00:18:22,900 --> 00:18:25,200
I won't fight anymore.

307
00:18:26,500 --> 00:18:28,067
Come here.

308
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:29,567
Hurry!

309
00:18:32,433 --> 00:18:33,833
There!

310
00:18:41,933 --> 00:18:43,633
Quick!

311
00:18:43,767 --> 00:18:45,700
Go, go!

312
00:18:51,200 --> 00:18:53,633
Don't rush. Take it easy.

313
00:18:55,267 --> 00:18:56,900
Stay here!

314
00:18:57,033 --> 00:18:58,200
Don't look back!

315
00:19:22,167 --> 00:19:24,200
- Don't!
- You're dead now.

316
00:19:24,333 --> 00:19:25,267
Don't!

317
00:19:30,033 --> 00:19:31,867
Go ahead, try it!

318
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:34,900
You're going to fall straight
into hell, Mando!

319
00:19:35,033 --> 00:19:35,800
Hey!

320
00:19:39,100 --> 00:19:40,400
Bok!

321
00:19:40,533 --> 00:19:42,400
Bok, help me.

322
00:19:42,533 --> 00:19:43,167
Bok!

323
00:19:43,300 --> 00:19:45,300
I'm running out of blood, Bok.

324
00:19:45,433 --> 00:19:47,200
- Bok...
- Bok!

325
00:19:47,333 --> 00:19:49,667
Please tell Doc Cecilia...

326
00:19:49,800 --> 00:19:52,733
that I'd love to be
her boyfriend.

327
00:19:52,867 --> 00:19:54,700
Bok, this is nothing serious.

328
00:19:54,833 --> 00:19:56,133
- Let's go!
- Bok...

329
00:19:56,267 --> 00:19:57,567
It's getting dark, Bok.

330
00:19:57,700 --> 00:19:59,500
What time is it, Bok?

331
00:19:59,633 --> 00:20:02,867
There's so much blood, Bok.

332
00:20:03,033 --> 00:20:05,833
It's like my grandmother's
calling me, Bok.

333
00:20:09,267 --> 00:20:10,500
- Bok!
- Let's go.

334
00:20:15,467 --> 00:20:17,067
Enriquez.

335
00:20:17,200 --> 00:20:18,433
Sir.

336
00:20:18,567 --> 00:20:19,700
How many escaped?

337
00:20:19,833 --> 00:20:22,133
I haven't confirmed
how many yet, Sir.

338
00:20:22,267 --> 00:20:25,633
Dizon, follow Conde and Garcia.

339
00:20:25,767 --> 00:20:26,967
Search the perimeter.

340
00:20:27,100 --> 00:20:28,467
The prisoners haven't
gone far yet.

341
00:20:28,600 --> 00:20:30,600
Yes, Sir. Let's go!
Move, move, move!

342
00:20:35,100 --> 00:20:36,500
Who's behind this?

343
00:20:36,633 --> 00:20:39,100
Mando Garrido, also known
as Mandong Warak, Sir,

344
00:20:39,233 --> 00:20:41,300
and Romel Salvador.

345
00:20:41,433 --> 00:20:42,533
Where are they?

346
00:20:42,667 --> 00:20:45,767
This is Romel Salvador.

347
00:20:45,900 --> 00:20:47,900
Where is Mandong Warak?

348
00:20:48,033 --> 00:20:49,733
He hasn't been caught yet, Sir.

349
00:20:56,467 --> 00:20:57,400
Sir, it's okay.

350
00:20:57,533 --> 00:20:59,433
I'll just get something.

351
00:21:02,733 --> 00:21:03,967
What did they say, Bok?

352
00:21:04,100 --> 00:21:06,600
Am I going to undergo surgery?

353
00:21:06,733 --> 00:21:08,600
You're not going
to have surgery.

354
00:21:08,767 --> 00:21:11,400
They just stitched up your wound
and cleaned it.

355
00:21:11,533 --> 00:21:12,967
They said you can be discharged
right away.

356
00:21:14,200 --> 00:21:15,267
What?

357
00:21:15,400 --> 00:21:17,467
- I'll be discharged now?
- Yes.

358
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:20,867
Bok, maybe you could ask
the doctor

359
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:24,133
to confine me for at least
three days and two nights.

360
00:21:25,667 --> 00:21:28,100
What's this? A vacation?

361
00:21:28,233 --> 00:21:29,967
Why do you want to be confined?

362
00:21:32,133 --> 00:21:33,767
You're really slow, Bok.

363
00:21:33,900 --> 00:21:38,033
Of course, if Doc Cecilia
finds out that I'm confined,

364
00:21:38,167 --> 00:21:39,533
she'll come here.

365
00:21:39,667 --> 00:21:44,067
Then I'll make a move on her,
right?

366
00:21:44,233 --> 00:21:46,000
She won't visit you.

367
00:21:46,133 --> 00:21:47,367
She already has a boyfriend,
right?

368
00:21:47,500 --> 00:21:49,367
It's the vice mayor.

369
00:21:49,500 --> 00:21:51,933
Bok...

370
00:21:52,067 --> 00:21:57,267
Don't underestimate
the power of mercy.

371
00:21:57,400 --> 00:21:59,367
Doc Cecilia won't be able
to do anything

372
00:21:59,500 --> 00:22:03,167
when she sees my sad face.

373
00:22:03,300 --> 00:22:04,633
Like this.

374
00:22:10,833 --> 00:22:12,400
You're really crazy.

375
00:22:12,533 --> 00:22:13,633
Mando and the others
have escaped already,

376
00:22:13,767 --> 00:22:15,500
and that's what you're thinking.

377
00:22:15,667 --> 00:22:17,367
Oh, by the way...

378
00:22:17,500 --> 00:22:19,000
What's the update about Mando
and the others?

379
00:22:19,133 --> 00:22:21,000
Do they know where he is?

380
00:22:21,133 --> 00:22:22,333
Not yet.

381
00:22:22,467 --> 00:22:25,567
That's why I'll call the chief
and get an update.

382
00:22:25,700 --> 00:22:26,967
Wait, I'll just call him first.

383
00:22:27,100 --> 00:22:28,467
Okay.

384
00:22:29,500 --> 00:22:32,700
How should I put on a sad face?

385
00:22:32,833 --> 00:22:35,000
No, duck face is the trend now.

386
00:22:52,700 --> 00:22:55,133
Sir, can I talk to Enriquez?

387
00:22:55,267 --> 00:22:57,133
- Hello, Sir?
- How are you? Are you okay?

388
00:22:57,267 --> 00:22:58,267
Are you hurt?

389
00:22:58,400 --> 00:22:59,767
No, Sir. I'm okay.

390
00:22:59,900 --> 00:23:03,067
Where did you get the pimple
patch drugs earlier?

391
00:23:03,200 --> 00:23:04,900
In Anika's makeup bag.

392
00:23:05,033 --> 00:23:05,833
Anika?

393
00:23:05,967 --> 00:23:07,967
You're not putting this on me,
Jhem.

394
00:23:08,100 --> 00:23:10,000
I bought the pimple patch
from you, remember?

395
00:23:10,133 --> 00:23:11,600
Maybe you forgot about that.

396
00:23:11,733 --> 00:23:12,800
Are you here for Faye?

397
00:23:12,933 --> 00:23:14,067
Oh, no, Vice.

398
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:15,767
Will and I are undercover
agents.

399
00:23:15,900 --> 00:23:16,800
Do you love him?

400
00:23:16,933 --> 00:23:17,967
What do you mean?

401
00:23:18,100 --> 00:23:18,867
Let me change the question.

402
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:19,900
Are you happy with him?

403
00:23:20,033 --> 00:23:21,167
What's the update with Mando?

404
00:23:21,300 --> 00:23:22,567
It's not that I'm getting
ahead of you

405
00:23:22,733 --> 00:23:24,233
or questioning your abilities,

406
00:23:24,367 --> 00:23:26,767
but why are you helping
that guy?

407
00:23:26,900 --> 00:23:28,800
Because he never fails.

408
00:23:28,933 --> 00:23:31,667
I've never given him a job
that he can't finish.

409
00:23:31,800 --> 00:23:32,800
Conde!
